Rating: 3
People always love this garlic bread. It has enough garlic which many times garlic bread does not. I have always made garlic bread this way but for one change. Bake the bread in a brown paper bag clipped with a clothespin. This gives it a crispy crust. Don't leave it in the oven too long, or it will not be soft in the middle. If you don't have a clothespin, a paper clip will do, but that is harder to get off when it's hot. You can even staple it, but that too is harder to get off.

